supportDesc.extent: Part I: Folios 2-117. Part II: Folios 118-180.;

layoutDesc.layout: Part I: 1 column(s); ruled lines: 28-36; written lines: 28-36; Uniform layout. Catchwords on every verso. Some extensive notes in the margins, see e.g., foliosIrregular fol 48r-55v. Part II: 1 column(s); ruled lines: 28; written lines: 28; Uniform layout. Initial words in square characters. Catchwords on every verso.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Part I: Sefardi semi-cursive script of the 15th to 16th century.Part II: Italian semi-cursive of the 16th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine: 'En Shemesh and Sepher Hai-Yichud. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 27,002.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Giuseppe Almanzi (b. 1801, d. 1860), bibliophile; his manuscript no. 113: his library including 322 medieval Hebrew manuscripts were purchased en bloc by the British Museum in October 1865 for £1,000 through Asher & Co., Berlin dealer to the British Museum (see 131-153): inscribed, folio [182v] (fse002v).
